               <msContents class="#STM">
                  <summary><p>The <title xml:lang="ta">Vikkiramārkaṉ Katai</title> alias the <title xml:lang="ta">Vikkiramātittaṉ Katai</title>. The text is incomplete (stops abruptly in U2c, f[217]v7). The folios are, unless rare exceptions, not foliated and unblackened. The bundle seems to be disordered at its end. Several hands. By at least one Christian copyist, as attested by a Christian blessing and Christian cross symbols.</p>
<p>The incipit in U2c is a corrupt version of the Vijayanagara kings's titulature.</p>
<p>Description based on the examination of the original manuscript (December 2020).</p>
<p>Dimensions assessed at the time of examination.</p>      </summary>
                  
